WEBVTT

00:02.293 --> 00:03.556
You'll never believe
what happened to me

00:03.557 --> 00:04.479
at work today.
Hmm?

00:04.480 --> 00:07.481
This old guy was choking on
his food, and I saved his life.

00:07.483 --> 00:08.932
You're kidding.
Did you Heimlich him?

00:08.934 --> 00:11.368
No. I said, "Oh, my God,
I think that old guy's choking,"

00:11.370 --> 00:13.370
and then one of the busboys
Heimlich'ed him.

00:15.874 --> 00:17.441
You're a hero.

00:17.443 --> 00:21.295
Yeah, that <i>was</i>
the point of the story.

00:21.297 --> 00:22.997
Oh, yeah, speaking of work,
do you know

00:22.999 --> 00:24.398
if you have
Thursday night off?

00:24.400 --> 00:25.949
Um, I think so. Why?

00:25.951 --> 00:27.951
What do you mean, why?
It's Valentine's Day.

00:27.953 --> 00:29.220
Oh, right.

00:29.222 --> 00:30.504
Yeah, we can do something.

00:30.506 --> 00:33.173
You could be
a little more into it.

00:33.175 --> 00:34.975
No, I'm into it, I'm into it.

00:34.977 --> 00:36.560
Just, there's so much pressure
to make the night special,

00:36.562 --> 00:38.262
and it never works out.

00:38.264 --> 00:40.464
Okay, well, this time
it's going to be different.

00:40.466 --> 00:42.616
Because I am
like a romance ninja.

00:44.469 --> 00:46.237
You don't see it coming,
and then bam!

00:46.239 --> 00:49.440
Romance, watch out, hearts,
kisses, love, ooh-ya!

00:50.408 --> 00:51.975
You know,
sometimes I think I've made you

00:51.977 --> 00:53.644
so much cooler
than you used to be,

00:53.646 --> 00:55.246
and then you go and do that.

00:57.649 --> 00:58.999
So, in conclusion,

00:59.001 --> 01:01.752
I believe the painful
sensation felt

01:01.754 --> 01:04.154
after passing a meal
of spicy chilies

01:04.156 --> 01:08.325
is proof that the rectum does
possess the sense of taste.

01:13.882 --> 01:15.883
I concur, but you
changed the subject.

01:15.885 --> 01:19.053
What are we doing
for Valentine's Day?

01:19.055 --> 01:21.438
Oh, you caught that,
did you?

01:22.941 --> 01:26.393
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:26.395 --> 01:29.863
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:29.865 --> 01:31.515
♪ The Earth began to cool

01:31.517 --> 01:34.401
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:34.403 --> 01:36.603
♪ We built the Wall
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:36.605 --> 01:39.456
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:39.458 --> 01:41.292
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:41.294 --> 01:43.093
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

01:43.118 --> 01:47.118
