01:53.193 --> 01:54.910
Okay.

01:55.262 --> 01:56.296
Okay.

01:58.132 --> 01:59.382
Okay.

02:00.384 --> 02:01.601
Okay.

02:02.286 --> 02:04.220
Okay!

02:07.341 --> 02:08.491
Okay.

02:11.638 --> 02:12.970
Everything okay?

02:16.692 --> 02:18.393
Bernie's a little cranky

02:18.395 --> 02:20.511
since she's been working,
like, 17 hours a day.

02:20.513 --> 02:23.030
And I've got a lot on my plate,
too, because I've been

02:23.032 --> 02:25.116
busting my tail
playing <i>Assassin's Creed.</i>

02:25.118 --> 02:26.734
Hey, Stuart,

02:26.736 --> 02:28.403
you got anything going on
for Valentine's Day?

02:28.405 --> 02:29.687
Not really.

02:29.689 --> 02:32.189
Other than hiding all
the sharp objects around here

02:32.191 --> 02:34.876
and white-knuckling it
till morning.

02:34.878 --> 02:36.043
What do you got going on?

02:36.045 --> 02:38.362
Oh, well, I was going
to spend the night

02:38.364 --> 02:40.164
with my special little lady,
but, uh,

02:40.166 --> 02:43.868
she got worms, and then I
had to take her to the vet.

02:47.139 --> 02:48.589
There must be something
we can do.

02:48.591 --> 02:51.592
Well, uh, how about you keep
the store open late,

02:51.594 --> 02:53.594
and we throw a party
for all the people

02:53.596 --> 02:54.595
who don't have dates?

02:54.597 --> 02:57.014
That actually sounds
kind of nice.

02:57.016 --> 02:58.900
Yeah, the theme will be
that the greatest love

02:58.902 --> 03:03.104
a man can have
is the love he has with himself.

03:04.623 --> 03:06.190
That's good.

03:06.192 --> 03:10.995
Or maybe something a little less
"hand in the pants."

03:13.198 --> 03:14.532
Oh, Alex, excellent.

03:14.534 --> 03:16.918
I have a research problem

03:16.920 --> 03:18.786
that I believe
you can help with.

03:18.788 --> 03:20.505
Oh, Dr. Cooper, thank you.

03:20.507 --> 03:22.290
I've been waiting
for an opportunity

03:22.292 --> 03:24.175
to contribute
to your scientific work.

03:24.177 --> 03:27.678
Oh, no, no.
That's not going to happen, no.

03:28.881 --> 03:32.967
What I need you to do
is find a Valentine's gift

03:32.969 --> 03:35.353
for my girlfriend.

03:35.355 --> 03:37.355
You realize I passed up
an opportunity

03:37.357 --> 03:40.274
to work at Fermilab
to take this job with you.

03:40.276 --> 03:43.978
Well, I guess those chaps
will have to have

03:43.980 --> 03:46.230
someone else buy
their girlfriends presents.

03:46.232 --> 03:47.448
Now, here is...

03:47.450 --> 03:50.151
Let's see.

03:50.153 --> 03:51.652
This is...

03:55.224 --> 03:57.358
This is about $2,000.

03:57.360 --> 03:58.960
Um, I think

03:58.962 --> 04:02.880
she likes monkeys
and the color gray.

04:09.004 --> 04:11.339
Contribute to my work.

04:13.091 --> 04:17.461
Ah, kids say
the darnedest things.

04:19.565 --> 04:20.848
Hey, you coming
to lunch?

04:20.850 --> 04:21.933
Yeah, one second.

04:21.935 --> 04:23.267
Come here. I want
to show you something.

04:23.269 --> 04:24.301
What you looking at?

04:24.303 --> 04:26.354
Well, I was trying
to come up with something

04:26.356 --> 04:28.639
really romantic
to give Bernadette

04:28.641 --> 04:29.991
for Valentine's Day
since she's been

04:29.993 --> 04:32.493
such a pain in the ass.

04:35.146 --> 04:37.698
You can't find a
card that says that?

04:37.700 --> 04:39.166
Check it out.

04:39.168 --> 04:40.835
I used the
atomic force microscope

04:40.837 --> 04:44.422
in the material science lab
and wrote our initials

04:44.424 --> 04:47.542
in a heart 1/1,000
the size of a grain of sand.

04:48.510 --> 04:50.678
Oh, that's cool.

04:50.680 --> 04:55.349
A micro-valentine
for a microbiologist.

04:55.351 --> 04:58.102
From her micro-husband.

05:01.673 --> 05:02.690
That is amazing.

05:02.692 --> 05:04.559
How long did this take you?

05:04.561 --> 05:06.811
Mmm, about 12 hours.

05:06.813 --> 05:08.279
I pulled an all-nighter.

05:08.281 --> 05:09.346
Oh, wow.

05:09.348 --> 05:11.198
Yeah, I know,
it really took a bite

05:11.200 --> 05:13.484
out of my video game time.

05:13.486 --> 05:15.319
What are you
and Penny doing?

05:15.321 --> 05:17.655
Oh, I'm going to take her to
a nice restaurant for dinner.

05:17.657 --> 05:21.025
Oh, that's not bad,
but as far as romance goes,

05:21.027 --> 05:23.544
I think my gift hits it
right out of...

05:27.382 --> 05:29.216
Want to come to
dinner with us?

05:29.218 --> 05:30.885
Yes, please.

05:32.971 --> 05:34.371
Okay.

05:34.373 --> 05:36.257
Amy will be
here shortly,

05:36.259 --> 05:39.677
expecting the perfect
Valentine's gift, so...

05:39.679 --> 05:41.012
you're up kid.

05:41.014 --> 05:43.097
Dazzle me. Go.

05:43.099 --> 05:45.683
Okay, I think I have
some really great choices.

05:45.685 --> 05:47.652
I went on Amy's
Facebook page

05:47.654 --> 05:49.353
and read up on her interests.

05:49.355 --> 05:52.023
Now, see, I never would have
thought to do that.

05:53.058 --> 05:54.492
Clearly, I made a good choice

05:54.494 --> 05:55.726
farming this out to you.

05:55.728 --> 05:58.412
But I am telling you,
Amy hit the boyfriend jackpot.

05:58.414 --> 06:01.198
Anyway, my socks are on.

06:01.200 --> 06:02.750
Let's knock them off.

06:07.589 --> 06:09.874
Well, um, I know she loves
playing the harp,

06:09.876 --> 06:14.929
so I found this
beautiful music box

06:14.931 --> 06:16.847
that plays one
of her favorite songs.

06:19.551 --> 06:21.953
Now, Amy already
has a real harp.

06:23.021 --> 06:25.756
And it can play any song.

06:25.758 --> 06:28.359
What are you trying
to pull here?

06:29.127 --> 06:30.645
No, I just thought
it would be...

06:30.647 --> 06:32.563
Next.

06:33.398 --> 06:34.732
Okay.

06:34.734 --> 06:37.068
Um, I know she's a fan
of <i>The Canterbury Tales,</i>

06:37.070 --> 06:40.321
Mmm.
so I found...

06:40.323 --> 06:41.906
this cool map

06:41.908 --> 06:43.908
that illustrates the character's
journey through England.

06:43.910 --> 06:46.276
I thought we could put it
in a really nice frame.

06:46.278 --> 06:50.631
But she's got Google Maps
on her phone.

06:54.369 --> 06:56.453
I don't know
how to respond to that.

06:57.839 --> 06:59.924
Well, I hope it's
with a third good option,

06:59.926 --> 07:02.593
because these first two... blah.

07:04.396 --> 07:06.313
Okay.

07:06.315 --> 07:09.233
Well, uh, luckily,
I saved the best for last.

07:10.301 --> 07:11.352
Since Amy's a neuroscientist,

07:11.354 --> 07:13.187
I did some research
and found out

07:13.189 --> 07:14.805
that Santiago Ramón y Cajal,

07:14.807 --> 07:16.807
the father
of modern neuroscience,

07:16.809 --> 07:19.360
did lots of hand drawings
of brain cells.

07:19.362 --> 07:22.146
And I managed
to find

07:22.148 --> 07:25.583
this signed print.

07:25.585 --> 07:27.835
Wow.

07:27.837 --> 07:29.620
Oh, this is truly remarkable.

07:29.622 --> 07:31.539
Thank you.

07:31.541 --> 07:33.007
I think I'll keep it for myself.

07:36.845 --> 07:38.328
What about your girlfriend?

07:38.330 --> 07:40.131
It's too late.
I call dibs.

07:44.352 --> 07:46.971
This place is
really beautiful.

07:46.973 --> 07:49.223
Wah... romance ninja.

07:52.310 --> 07:53.360
Hey.

07:53.362 --> 07:55.062
Sorry we're late.

07:55.064 --> 07:56.447
No problem.
We just sat down.

07:56.449 --> 07:58.182
Mmm, would you like some wine?

07:58.184 --> 07:59.366
Yeah, fill her up.

08:01.686 --> 08:03.687
I'll tell you when to stop.

08:05.891 --> 08:07.291
Is everything okay?

08:07.293 --> 08:09.026
Terrific.
Couldn't be better.

08:09.028 --> 08:10.661
Oh, bite me.

08:12.497 --> 08:14.215
Look, we can still
have a nice night.

08:14.217 --> 08:15.499
Just tell me where it is.

08:15.501 --> 08:16.667
Maybe if you did what you said

08:16.669 --> 08:18.219
you were going to do,
I'd tell you.

08:19.004 --> 08:20.370
Uh, where what is?

08:20.372 --> 08:22.840
She hid my Xbox
like I'm a child.

08:24.059 --> 08:26.227
Yeah, and my mom got me
that for my birthday,

08:26.229 --> 08:28.712
so if you don't give
it back, I'm telling.

08:29.931 --> 08:31.548
I've been working
late every night.

08:31.550 --> 08:33.100
All I asked was that he

08:33.102 --> 08:34.852
clean the apartment
and do one load of laundry.

08:34.854 --> 08:36.070
But did he do it? No.

08:36.072 --> 08:37.888
He just kept on
playing that stupid game.

08:37.890 --> 08:39.523
You like pushing
buttons so much,

08:39.525 --> 08:41.991
try pushing them
on the washing machine.

08:43.727 --> 08:45.329
I said I'm sorry.

08:45.331 --> 08:48.415
Sorry doesn't clean
my underpants, buddy.

08:49.451 --> 08:52.670
I told you, turn
them inside out.

08:52.672 --> 08:55.906
And I told you to bite me.

08:55.908 --> 08:59.576
Trying to have
a magical night here, guys.

09:03.381 --> 09:04.581
Oh, son of a bitch.

09:04.583 --> 09:05.966
What?

09:05.968 --> 09:07.384
Nothing. Nothing.

09:07.386 --> 09:08.552
No, tell me.

09:08.554 --> 09:10.921
It's just this guy
I used to date.

09:11.756 --> 09:12.923
Oh.

09:12.925 --> 09:14.942
Until he cheated on me
with my friend Gretchen,

09:14.944 --> 09:16.443
who's here with him now.

09:16.445 --> 09:17.695
You're kidding.

09:17.697 --> 09:20.748
And it looks like she lost
a lot of weight, damn it.

09:22.901 --> 09:24.285
I know it's not ideal,

09:24.287 --> 09:25.786
but don't let them
ruin our night.

09:25.788 --> 09:27.037
No, you're totally right.

09:27.039 --> 09:29.540
She could be skinny
'cause she's dying.

09:30.441 --> 09:32.609
That's the spirit.

09:32.611 --> 09:33.878
You know what, screw them.

09:33.880 --> 09:35.612
Our night is going to be
way more special than theirs.

09:35.614 --> 09:37.281
Yeah.

09:38.583 --> 09:39.750
Uh-oh.

09:40.719 --> 09:42.419
What?

09:43.288 --> 09:46.590
Oh, you got to be kidding me.

09:46.592 --> 09:47.558
Oh, my God, yes.

09:47.560 --> 09:48.843
Of course
I'll marry you.

09:51.263 --> 09:52.544
Two can play this game.

09:52.546 --> 09:53.457
Penny...
Get up.

09:53.458 --> 09:55.008
All right.

