10:05.402 --> 10:06.936
It's nice that
all the people

10:06.938 --> 10:08.438
who are lonely
on Valentine's Day

10:08.440 --> 10:10.440
can come here tonight
and be together.

10:10.442 --> 10:13.109
Yeah, I'm really
looking forward to it.

10:13.111 --> 10:15.862
In fact, there's no place
I would rather be than here.

10:15.864 --> 10:17.646
Except on a date with anybody.

10:17.648 --> 10:19.365
Literally anybody.

10:20.817 --> 10:23.202
You know, you and I have
so much fun hanging out.

10:23.204 --> 10:24.337
If you were a girl,

10:24.339 --> 10:26.372
all our problems
would be solved.

10:29.777 --> 10:31.144
What?

10:31.146 --> 10:32.595
Oh, yeah, think about it.

10:32.597 --> 10:33.996
We'd hang out,

10:33.998 --> 10:36.049
we'd read comic books,
we'd see movies.

10:36.051 --> 10:38.667
It'd be like the best
relationship ever.

10:38.669 --> 10:41.220
That does sound nice.

10:41.222 --> 10:43.839
Then I'd take you home,
slip off your little black dress

10:43.841 --> 10:47.176
and just pile-drive you
into oblivion.

10:49.530 --> 10:51.330
What?

10:52.483 --> 10:54.233
Oh, I can't believe

10:54.235 --> 10:57.203
he's going to marry the girl
he cheated on me with.

10:57.205 --> 10:58.237
Isn't it kind of nice?

10:58.239 --> 10:59.855
I mean, he was with
the wrong person,

10:59.857 --> 11:01.240
and now he found
the right person.

11:01.242 --> 11:02.992
What, so I'm the <i>wrong</i> person?

11:02.994 --> 11:05.211
Maybe you want to be
with Gretchen, too.

11:06.630 --> 11:08.664
They do look happy.

11:08.666 --> 11:09.865
Yeah, maybe tonight.

11:09.867 --> 11:11.217
But a year from
now, he'll be

11:11.219 --> 11:13.836
crawling under the sink
looking for his Xbox.

11:14.704 --> 11:16.539
Well, he will.

11:17.707 --> 11:19.976
You know what? Why don't we
just forget about them

11:19.978 --> 11:21.544
and enjoy our Valentine's Day?

11:21.546 --> 11:23.262
Yes, absolutely.

11:29.237 --> 11:30.603
Now they're doing that phony

11:30.605 --> 11:32.855
link-arm-drink thingy.

11:32.857 --> 11:35.908
I totally taught him that.

11:36.744 --> 11:38.494
I thought we were
letting it go.

11:38.496 --> 11:40.780
We were; it's just...
it's not fair, okay?

11:40.782 --> 11:41.998
They're bad people.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.366
It's not supposed to end
happy for them;

11:43.368 --> 11:44.751
it's supposed to end
happy for me.

11:44.753 --> 11:46.536
Um...

11:46.538 --> 11:47.954
it did end happy for you.

11:47.956 --> 11:48.921
You're here with me.

11:48.923 --> 11:51.507
Yeah, yeah, I know.

11:51.509 --> 11:54.043
Okay, this is getting a little
hard to not take personally.

11:54.045 --> 11:55.595
Oh, come on, don't
make this about you.

11:55.597 --> 11:57.180
Oh, I'm not.
It's about you.

11:57.182 --> 11:58.264
Yeah, well, whatever, okay?

11:58.266 --> 11:59.799
I told you,
Valentine's Day sucks.

11:59.801 --> 12:01.768
This one does,
and you're the reason why.

12:01.770 --> 12:03.186
What?

12:03.188 --> 12:05.471
You know, compared to them,

12:05.473 --> 12:06.806
I'm feeling
pretty good about us.

12:06.808 --> 12:08.391
Me, too.

12:08.393 --> 12:11.144
How about we blow off
dessert, go home early...

12:11.146 --> 12:12.228
I'll do that laundry.

12:12.230 --> 12:13.596
Thank you.

12:13.598 --> 12:14.564
I love you.

12:14.566 --> 12:16.599
Love you, too.

12:16.601 --> 12:18.701
So where'd you hide it?

12:18.703 --> 12:20.620
Where you'd never look.

12:20.622 --> 12:23.873
Damn it, it's in the
washing machine.

12:30.780 --> 12:31.780
Hello.

12:31.782 --> 12:33.466
Hello.

12:33.468 --> 12:35.051
Happy Valentine's Day.

12:35.053 --> 12:37.587
Okay.

12:39.556 --> 12:40.956
Shall we go to dinner?

12:40.958 --> 12:42.625
Hang on.

12:42.627 --> 12:44.927
As you know, I had planned
a traditional evening

12:44.929 --> 12:46.429
of romance and gifts.

12:46.431 --> 12:47.647
Yes,

12:47.649 --> 12:48.797
and as you know,

12:48.799 --> 12:51.434
I planned to pretend
to enjoy it.

12:52.569 --> 12:55.154
I've been working on
this facial expression all day.

12:57.441 --> 12:59.992
And I appreciate your effort,

12:59.994 --> 13:01.477
but upon contemplation,

13:01.479 --> 13:03.446
I decided I was being selfish.

13:03.448 --> 13:05.748
So, I canceled
our dinner reservations

13:05.750 --> 13:07.600
and came up
with an even better way

13:07.602 --> 13:09.168
to celebrate Valentine's Day.

13:09.170 --> 13:11.003
What is that?

13:11.005 --> 13:12.288
By doing none of it--

13:12.290 --> 13:13.456
no dinner,

13:13.458 --> 13:15.174
no romance, no gifts.

13:15.176 --> 13:17.793
We stay here,
order a pizza

13:17.795 --> 13:19.679
and watch one
of your beloved

13:19.681 --> 13:21.881
Star War Trek things.

13:23.050 --> 13:24.217
Really?

13:24.219 --> 13:25.568
Well, that's what

13:25.570 --> 13:26.702
you'd love, isn't it?

13:26.704 --> 13:28.337
More than anything.

13:28.339 --> 13:30.406
Well, then...

13:30.408 --> 13:32.341
that's what we're going to do.

13:34.228 --> 13:35.361
Well...

13:35.363 --> 13:37.313
I don't know what to say.

13:37.315 --> 13:39.848
This is the most thoughtful gift

13:39.850 --> 13:42.017
that anyone's ever given me.

13:42.019 --> 13:43.819
And that's including
an amazing gift

13:43.821 --> 13:45.738
that I gave myself
earlier today.

13:47.908 --> 13:50.326
I'm your girlfriend.
That's my job.

13:50.328 --> 13:53.963
And I know gift-giving
puts a lot of pressure on you,

13:53.965 --> 13:57.199
so whatever you got me,
you can return.

13:58.802 --> 14:00.419
No.

14:00.421 --> 14:03.222
No, after everything you
didn't do for me tonight,

14:03.224 --> 14:04.974
I want you to have it.

14:05.893 --> 14:06.826
What's this?

14:06.828 --> 14:08.544
Read it.

14:08.546 --> 14:09.845
"Sheldon Cooper,

14:09.847 --> 14:12.315
Caltech University
employee information"?

14:12.317 --> 14:13.516
At the bottom.

14:13.518 --> 14:17.436
"In case of emergency,
please contact...

14:17.438 --> 14:19.655
Amy Farrah Fowler."

14:21.775 --> 14:23.943
And there's my phone number.

14:26.914 --> 14:31.117
This is the most beautiful gift
you could've ever given me.

14:31.119 --> 14:32.618
Well, I thought,

14:32.620 --> 14:36.672
if I have a stroke
or a kidney stone,

14:36.674 --> 14:38.907
who would I want
to share that with?

14:42.429 --> 14:44.964
And you picked me.

14:44.966 --> 14:46.816
It's like you said--

14:46.818 --> 14:48.551
you're my girlfriend.

14:48.553 --> 14:49.885
Oh, Sheldon.

14:49.887 --> 14:51.687
Yeah...

14:54.608 --> 14:56.492
Okay.

14:56.494 --> 14:59.395
Stop ruining Valentine's Day
and order my pizza.

15:04.534 --> 15:05.601
Night.

15:05.603 --> 15:06.886
Yep.

15:15.329 --> 15:16.945
You know what?

15:16.947 --> 15:18.297
That was pretty
crappy of you.

15:18.299 --> 15:21.634
I mean, all I wanted to do
was give you a great night,

15:21.636 --> 15:24.170
and it's like you-you went out
of your way to destroy it.

15:24.172 --> 15:25.421
Yeah, I know.

15:25.423 --> 15:26.756
I'm a total bitch.

15:26.758 --> 15:28.574
I'm not saying that.
Well, I am.

15:28.576 --> 15:30.593
Fine, you win.
You're a bitch.

15:32.596 --> 15:35.147
Why couldn't we
just have a nice time?

15:35.149 --> 15:37.600
I don't know.

15:37.602 --> 15:40.353
Maybe 'cause things are going
so well between us lately

15:40.355 --> 15:42.304
and I've been really happy.

15:48.111 --> 15:51.831
Okay, you're gonna have to make
a lot more sense than that.

15:51.833 --> 15:55.651
Obviously, I have
some commitment issues.

15:55.653 --> 15:58.204
Glaringly obvious.
Go on.

15:58.206 --> 15:59.988
As long as things keep going
great between us,

15:59.990 --> 16:01.424
you'll keep asking me
to marry you,

16:01.426 --> 16:02.958
and eventually I'm gonna
end up saying yes,

16:02.960 --> 16:04.593
and then we're gonna be
married forever,

16:04.595 --> 16:07.430
and the whole thing
just freaks me out.

16:09.350 --> 16:11.467
Okay.

16:11.469 --> 16:13.719
I know I propose a lot.

16:17.524 --> 16:19.725
So how about this?

16:21.311 --> 16:24.897
I promise I will never ask you
to marry me again.

16:24.899 --> 16:26.816
What... what do you mean?

16:26.818 --> 16:28.367
Are you breaking up with me?

16:28.369 --> 16:29.402
No.

16:29.404 --> 16:30.569
No, no, no, no.

16:30.571 --> 16:33.122
But if someday you decide
you want to get married,

16:33.124 --> 16:34.874
you have to propose to me.

16:35.675 --> 16:37.526
Really?
Yes.

16:37.528 --> 16:39.378
It's all on you.

16:39.380 --> 16:41.530
But I got to tell you,
when the time comes,

16:41.532 --> 16:42.715
I want the whole nine yards.

16:42.717 --> 16:44.417
I want you down
on one knee, flowers.

16:44.419 --> 16:46.502
I want to be swept off my feet.

16:48.772 --> 16:50.072
Yeah, you got it.

16:50.074 --> 16:51.257
And I'm cool with surprises.

16:51.259 --> 16:54.326
But nothing on a Jumbotron.

16:54.328 --> 16:57.063
I don't want to cry
on a big screen like that.

16:59.266 --> 17:00.483
Okay.

17:02.853 --> 17:04.319
You know what?

17:04.321 --> 17:06.221
This might be the wine talking,

17:06.223 --> 17:09.575
but I have a very important
question to ask you.

17:10.444 --> 17:11.926
You do?

17:12.762 --> 17:14.630
Leonard Hofstadter...

17:15.464 --> 17:16.665
Yes?

17:18.268 --> 17:20.903
...will you be my valentine?

17:22.839 --> 17:24.623
Sorry. Maybe next year.

17:27.794 --> 17:28.928
I'm just kidding!

17:28.930 --> 17:31.464
Romance ninja.
Let's have sex! Wah!

17:36.137 --> 17:37.603
Thank you, guys,
for doing this.

17:37.605 --> 17:39.271
We're glad you
could make it.

17:39.273 --> 17:42.274
Usually I spend Valentine's Day
sad and alone.

17:42.276 --> 17:44.760
This year, I'm just sad.

17:47.096 --> 17:49.431
What is it about this holiday
that makes people so unhappy?

17:49.433 --> 17:50.399
I know.

17:50.401 --> 17:52.118
I hate myself
most of the time,

17:52.120 --> 17:55.738
but tonight's the night
I know everyone else does, too.

17:55.740 --> 17:57.957
I think you're cool.

17:58.792 --> 18:00.993
Great.

18:03.046 --> 18:04.547
I got to tell you,

18:04.549 --> 18:07.282
we've got to stop beating
ourselves up like this.

18:08.802 --> 18:10.703
Excuse me, everybody.

18:10.705 --> 18:12.271
Can I have your attention,
please?

18:17.394 --> 18:19.595
We're all here tonight
because...

18:19.597 --> 18:22.181
we have no one to be with.

18:22.183 --> 18:26.986
But... that doesn't
make us mutants.

18:26.988 --> 18:29.989
The only mutants here
are in these comic books.

18:31.858 --> 18:35.077
We've got to stop defining
our self-worth

18:35.079 --> 18:37.663
by whether or not
we're in a relationship.

18:38.665 --> 18:40.950
You know what I see
when I look around?

18:42.068 --> 18:44.036
I see a room
full of great people.

18:46.106 --> 18:48.340
So let's give ourselves a break.

18:48.342 --> 18:50.593
We are a community,

18:50.595 --> 18:51.760
and as long
as we have

18:51.762 --> 18:53.345
each other,

18:53.347 --> 18:55.497
we're never truly alone.

19:02.722 --> 19:04.006
That was cool.

19:04.008 --> 19:05.858
What you said.

19:05.860 --> 19:08.110
You really think so?

19:08.112 --> 19:09.728
Yeah, I do.

19:09.730 --> 19:10.896
Thank you.

19:13.416 --> 19:15.034
Uh...

19:15.036 --> 19:16.351
Would you like to, uh...

19:16.353 --> 19:19.405
get a cup...
a cup of coffee or...?

19:19.407 --> 19:21.240
Okay.

19:26.713 --> 19:28.747
Later, losers!

19:45.139 --> 19:47.390
Hello?

19:47.392 --> 19:49.209
Another medical emergency?

19:49.211 --> 19:52.045
What's wrong with him now?

19:52.047 --> 19:55.949
I seriously doubt he was bitten
by a Chinese bird spider.

19:57.568 --> 20:00.186
How exactly does a bump
feel Asian?

20:01.822 --> 20:04.073
Just put him on the phone.

20:04.075 --> 20:06.359
Sheldon, I am not driving
over there again.

20:07.194 --> 20:08.745
Because I drove
over there yesterday

20:08.747 --> 20:10.713
for a brain tumor
that turned out to be

20:10.715 --> 20:12.999
an ice cream headache.

20:13.001 --> 20:17.086
Yes, I still want to be
your emergency contact.

20:18.556 --> 20:21.808
Yes, you can eat
your ice cream too fast

20:21.810 --> 20:24.010
and also have a brain tumor.

20:26.880 --> 20:29.048
I'm on my way.

20:30.818 --> 20:32.519
Brain tumor
would explain a lot.

